 those to the Syriac version as well. He concludes that there is unity of doctrine between the changes and additions of all the textual witnesses. Therefore he can refer to ‛the expanded text’.The teachings on afterlife as found in the various stages of the text of Ben Sira are compared with the teachings found in Jewish literature from about 200 B.C. until 100 A.D., both canonical – especially Daniel and the Wisdom of Solomon –, and apocryphal or pseudepigraphical, such as 1–2 Enoch, 4 Ezra, Jubilees, Psalms of Solomon, and Testaments of the XII Patriarchs.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aFuture lifexBiblical teaching. 4aEcclesiasticus. 4aEschatologie. 4aJesus Sirach. 4aPseudepigraphen. 4aTextgeschichte. 7aRELIGION / Biblical Criticism & Interpretation / Old Testament.2bisacsh  aApocrypha.  aBen Sira.  aEschatology.  aPseudepigrapha.1 aBeentjes, Pancratius C., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeentjes, Pancratius C., eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aCalduch-Benages, Nuria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCalduch-Benages, Núria, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGilbert, Maurice, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKearns, Conleth J., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aNorton, Gerard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Theology and Religious Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311023854908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Theology and Religious Studies 2000 